---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — RunningOut"
  description="Privacy policy for RunningOut, a free running tracker for iPhone and Apple Watch by Dale Hurley."
  keywords="RunningOut, privacy policy, running app, health data, HealthKit"
  ogType="website"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-b from-[#FF750F]/20 via-[#FF750F]/10 to-white dark:from-[#FF750F]/10 dark:via-[#FF750F]/5 dark:to-gray-900 pt-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-24 sm:py-32 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#FF750F] mb-4">RunningOut</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white sm:text-5xl">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        RunningOut is built for runners, not advertisers. Here is exactly what is collected, why, and who sees it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Data privacy banner -->
  <div class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-950 border-y border-green-200 dark:border-green-800">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-8 lg:px-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center gap-4 text-center sm:text-left">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 text-2xl" aria-hidden="true">
        &#x1F512;
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-semibold text-green-900 dark:text-green-100">Your data never leaves your Apple devices</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-green-800 dark:text-green-300">RunningOut collects nothing. All your runs, health metrics, and personal data stay on your iPhone and in your private iCloud account — visible only to you.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="py-24 sm:py-32 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-gray dark:prose-invert prose-headings:font-bold prose-a:text-[#FF750F] max-w-none">

      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <p>
        RunningOut collects no data. Everything — your runs, health metrics, routes, notes, and personal information — stays exclusively on your iPhone and Apple Watch, and in your private iCloud account. Only you can see it. RunningOut operates no servers, has no access to your iCloud data, and contains no advertising, analytics SDKs, or third-party tracking of any kind.
      </p>

      <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
      <p>RunningOut stores the following data locally on your iPhone and Apple Watch:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Saved runs including distance, duration, pace, splits, and route coordinates</li>
        <li>HealthKit metrics read during and after a run: heart rate, cadence, running power, stride length, vertical oscillation, ground contact time, elevation, and calories</li>
        <li>Personal records derived from your run history</li>
        <li>Notes, tags, and run media you attach to a saved run</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>HealthKit</h2>
      <p>
        RunningOut requests access to Apple Health to read workout context and to save runs you record. The specific data types accessed depend on your device, watch model, and the permissions you grant. RunningOut reads health data only to show you stats, calculate zones, and provide recovery context. It writes running workouts and optional body mass samples only when you record a run or explicitly save a body mass entry. Health data is never transmitted to any server controlled by RunningOut or Dale Hurley.
      </p>

      <h2>Location</h2>
      <p>
        Location access is used for outdoor run tracking, route maps, distance, pace, and elevation. Background location is used only while a run is active. Route coordinates are saved locally and synced to your private iCloud account as described below. Location data is never shared with third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>Camera, photos, and microphone</h2>
      <p>
        Camera and photo library access are used only when you choose to capture or attach media to a run. Microphone access is used only when you record video. Media you attach is stored locally and optionally synced to your private iCloud account.
      </p>

      <h2>Apple Music</h2>
      <p>
        Apple Music access is used only to show songs played during a run on the post-run summary screen. RunningOut does not store or transmit music listening data.
      </p>

      <h2>iCloud sync</h2>
      <p>
        When iCloud is available and enabled, RunningOut syncs your run history through your private iCloud account using CloudKit. Synced data can include run history, routes, treadmill images, notes, tags, calories, and workout summaries. This sync occurs exclusively between your own devices through Apple's infrastructure. RunningOut has no access to your iCloud data and operates no servers that receive or store your information.
      </p>

      <h2>No third-party tracking</h2>
      <p>RunningOut contains no advertising SDKs, no analytics frameworks, and no third-party tracking identifiers. The app does not share any data with advertisers, data brokers, or analytics providers.</p>

      <h2>Deleting your data</h2>
      <p>
        You can delete all local app data from the iOS Settings app: open RunningOut settings, turn on Reset All Data, then launch RunningOut. This removes all locally stored runs, preferences, and cached data. To remove iCloud-synced data, delete the app from all devices associated with your Apple ID.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>RunningOut is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly collect data from children.</p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy changes materially, the updated version will be posted at this URL. The date at the bottom of this page reflects the most recent revision.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy? Reach out via the <a href="/runningout/support">support page</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-12">Last updated: April 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#4B0600] dark:bg-gray-800">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-orange-100">
        Questions or concerns?
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="/runningout/support"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-[#FF750F] text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-orange-500 transition-colors font-semibold"
        >
          Support
        </a>
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 border border-orange-400/40 text-orange-100 rounded-lg hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors font-semibold"
        >
          Back to home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
